Launching Gazebo
step1:
killall -9 gzserver
killall -9 gzclient

Now:

cd ~/ros2_ws
source install/setup.bash
ros2 launch my_robot_description gazebo.launch.py


If Gazebo says "Address already in use"

Run:

killall -9 gzserver
killall -9 gzclient
pkill -9 -f gazebo

Then launch again:

ros2 launch my_robot_description gazebo.launch.py

Step 5: Verify Robot Exists
In a new terminal:

cd ~/ros2_ws
source install/setup.bash

ros2 topic list

You should see ROS topics from your robot.

